@arschmitz We can call .toString() on all string-valued option names that are supposed to be translatable. That way, if the values are strings, well, nothing happens. However, you can replace the strings with objects that provide the .toString() method. The objects themselves could then be translation-aware. This would take care of translating the string upon insertion into the DOM.

If we need re-translation while the widget is already instantiated, we can probably achieve that with the widget's refresh() method.

We can then provide the translations themselves separately, maybe as a mobileinit handler.

